I suspect that this is a dupe of #106832 but I'll file anyway in case it isn't. Same behavior on stable 1.66.1 as on nightly.

```rust
trait HasRelatedType {
    type Related;
}

struct Foo;

impl HasRelatedType for Foo {
    type Related = Foo;
}

trait SomeTrait {
    // This:
    type Gat<A>: HasRelatedType<Related = Self::Gat<Foo>>
    where
        A: HasRelatedType<Related = Foo>;
        
    // behaves as though I had written `Self::Gat<A>` instead of
    // `Self::Gat<Foo>`, like this:
    
    // type Gat<A>: HasRelatedType<Related = Self::Gat<A>>
    // where
    //    A: HasRelatedType<Related = Foo>;
    
}

struct Bar<A>(A);

impl<A> HasRelatedType for Bar<A>
where
    A: HasRelatedType<Related = Foo>,
{
    // The appropriate definition for satisfying the constraint on
    // `Gat<A>`. This doesn't compile, when it should.
    type Related = Bar<Foo>;

    // The wrong definiton for satisfying the constraint on `Gat<A>`.
    // This compiles, but it shouldn't.
    // type Related = Bar<A>;
    
}

impl SomeTrait for () {

    type Gat<A> = Bar<A> where A: HasRelatedType<Related = Foo>;
}
```

This errors with:

```
error[[E0271]](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/error-index.html#E0271): type mismatch resolving `<Bar<A> as HasRelatedType>::Related == Bar<A>`
  --> src/lib.rs:44:19
   |
44 |     type Gat<A> = Bar<A> where A: HasRelatedType<Related = Foo>;
   |              -    ^^^^^^ type mismatch resolving `<Bar<A> as HasRelatedType>::Related == Bar<A>`
   |              |
   |              this type parameter
   |
note: expected this to be `Bar<A>`
  --> src/lib.rs:34:20
   |
34 |     type Related = Bar<Foo>;
   |                    ^^^^^^^^
   = note: expected struct `Bar<A>`
              found struct `Bar<Foo>`
note: required by a bound in `SomeTrait::Gat`
  --> src/lib.rs:13:33
   |
13 |     type Gat<A>: HasRelatedType<Related = Self::Gat<Foo>>
   |                                 ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ required by this bound in `SomeTrait::Gat`

For more information about this error, try `rustc --explain E0271`.
```

If you comment out `type Related = Bar<Foo>` and uncomment `type Related = Bar<A>` then it compiles.

Playground link: https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=2e9094e1a7ce8744229bd2380af72b11
